## Decision: Deploy Strict Allowlist Immediately

**Recommendation: Configure a strict CORS allowlist of known frontend origins — do not fail closed.**

### Rationale

| Approach | Security | Operational Impact | Verdict |
|----------|----------|-------------------|---------|
| Block all origins | High | Service disruption; breaks legitimate frontends | Too aggressive |
| Strict allowlist | High | Zero disruption; only approved origins work | **Preferred** |

### Implementation

```nginx
# Nginx config
add_header Access-Control-Allow-Origin "https://app.example.com" always;
# Additional trusted origins as needed
```

Or programmatically (Express example):
```javascript
const allowedOrigins = [
  'https://app.example.com',
  'https://admin.example.com'
];

app.use(cors({
  origin: (origin, callback) => {
    if (!origin || allowedOrigins.includes(origin)) {
      callback(null, true);
    } else {
      callback(new Error('CORS policy violation'));
    }
  },

## Decision: Token Bucket with Per-IP AND Per-Account Throttling

**Recommendation: Implement token bucket with dual limiting — per-IP and per-account/username.**

### Rationale

| Approach | Brute Force Protection | Memory Efficiency | Accuracy | Verdict |
|----------|------------------------|-------------------|----------|---------|
| Token bucket (per-IP only) | Moderate | High | Good | Incomplete |
| Sliding window only | High | Low (per-request storage) | Best | Overkill |
| **Dual token bucket** | **Excellent** | **Moderate** | **Good** | **Preferred** |

### Implementation

```nginx
# Nginx limit_req_zone - shared memory for token bucket
limit_req_zone $binary_remote_addr zone=login_ip:10m rate=5r/m;
limit_req_zone $binary_remote_addr$http_x_forwarded_user zone=login_user:10m rate=3r/m;

# Apply to login endpoint
location /api/auth/login {
    limit_req zone=login_ip burst=10 nodelay;
    limit_req zone=login_user burst=3 nodelay;
    proxy_pass http://backend;
}
```

```javascript
// Express + Redis token bucket example
const rateLimiter = {
  login: {
    ip: { capacity: 5, refillRate: 5/60 },  // 5 req/min
    user: { capacity: 3, refillRate: 3/60 }  // 3 req/min per username
  }
};
```

### Thresholds for Auth Endpoints

| Endpoint | Per-IP Limit | Per-Account Limit | Action on Exceed |
|----------|--------------|-------------------|------------------|
